<br>
Stationary higher level mobs that never leave a fixed spot may be a way to raise your Def Skill with little or no risk. <br>
<br>
Also talk to your exp group.  Root the mob and stand on it.  Mob will aggro the closest person.  As far as I can tell it doesn;t affect the hate list.  When root breaks the tank normally regains aggro. You can also just step away from the rooted mob to loose aggro.  Definitely safer than making the mob mad to make it beat on you.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uteenawarmheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teena Warmheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MMDN CSC Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#006400>(2/11/02 3:28:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Clerics and the Defense Skill</span><hr size=1> Another thing to consider is that a skill that is capped at 200 won't be able to be reached until 60, thus you will get a couple increases a level between 40 and 60.  My warrior's dodge was stuck at 140 for the longest time, until I hit 50 and then it started to go up again. (For those that it seems to be stuck no matter what you do) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukornaenathecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kornaena the cleric</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Veteran<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img 